2.Data Preparation:

fu = function(s){
  d=deathrates[which(deathrates$Area==s),]
  return (d)
}

On a construit une fonction qui prend en parametre un etat amricain et retourne la base de donnes correspondante .

3.Time Series:

3-1) Building the time series

On va appliquer sur lexemple de Florida pour voir la variation du taux de mortalit entre les annes 2005 et 2014

Florida=fu("Florida")
FloridaRate=Florida[,2]
Florida.ts=ts(FloridaRate,start =2005,frequency=1)
plot.ts(Florida.ts)

3-2) Vizualising the Time Series

plot

plot.ts(Florida.ts)

ACF

acf(Florida.ts)

Cest la reprsentation de lautocorrlation pour dterminer leffet temporelle par rapport un certain intervalle de confiance => On remarque que la plupart des rsidus sont dans cette intervalle de confiance

PACF

pacf(Florida.ts)

3-3) Testing the Stationarity of the series: Test de dickey fuller

library(astsa)
library(tseries)
adf.test(Florida.ts)

4-3) Building Inverse Distance Weight Matrix

4-3-1) Extracting the corrdinates of countries

library(ggmap)
for(i in 1:length(deathrates$Area))

{
  a=deathrates[i,"Area"]
  a=as.character(a)
  b=geocode(a,source="dsk")
  deathrates[i,"long"]=b$lon
  deathrates[i,"lat"]=b$lat
  
}
for(i in 1:length(deathrates$Area))
{
  deathrates$long[i]=deathrates$long[i]*pi/180
  deathrates$lat[i]=deathrates$lat[i]*pi/180
}

On a extracter les coordonnes de chaque etat en utilisant library ggmap et la fonction geocode et on a transformer ces coordonnes du degr en radian

4-3-2) Building the distance Matrix

Massachusetts=fu("Massachusetts")
New_York=fu("New York")
Maine=fu("Maine")
NH=fu("New Hampshire")
Vermont=fu("Vermont")
data2=rbind(Vermont[1,c(1,7,8)],New_York[1,c(1,7,8)],NH[1,c(1,7,8)],Massachusetts[1,c(1,7,8)],Maine[1,c(1,7,8)])
R = 6371
M=matrix(1:25,nrow=5)
for (i in 1:nrow(data2) )
{
  for (j in 1:nrow(data2) )
  {
    M[i,j]=R*acos(cos(data2$long[i]-data2$long[j])*cos(data2$lat[i])*cos(data2$lat[j])+(sin(data2$lat[i])*sin(data2$lat[j])))
  }
  
}

4-3-3) Building the Weight Matrix

S=matrix(1:25,nrow=5)
for (i in 1:5 )
{
  for (j in 1:5 )
  {
    if(i==1)
    {
    S[i,j]=(1/M[i,j])/(1/M[i,2]+1/M[i,3]+1/M[i,4]+1/M[i,5])
    }
    else if(i==2)
    {
      S[i,j]=(1/M[i,j])/(1/M[i,1]+1/M[i,3]+1/M[i,4]+1/M[i,5])
    }
    else if(i==3)
    {
      S[i,j]=(1/M[i,j])/(1/M[i,1]+1/M[i,2]+1/M[i,4]+1/M[i,5])
    }
    else if(i==4)
    {
      S[i,j]=(1/M[i,j])/(1/M[i,1]+1/M[i,3]+1/M[i,2]+1/M[i,5])
    }
    else if(i==5)
    {
      S[i,j]=(1/M[i,j])/(1/M[i,1]+1/M[i,3]+1/M[i,4]+1/M[i,2])
    }
    
  }
}
S[1,1]=S[2,2]=S[3,3]=S[4,4]=S[5,5]=0

4-5) GSTAR Model with Inverse Distance Weight Matrix

4-5-1) Creating the package GSTAR

GSTAR<-function(Data,W,p){   Series<-ts(Data) 
k<-ncol(Data)                                   
# Number Location   
n<-nrow(Data)                                 
# Number Time   
zt<-(stack(as.data.frame(t(Data)))[,1])          
# Zt with Lag   
# Function Create Lag Data   
###########################################  
MD<-function(zt){     M<-matrix(0,(n*k),k)    
z=0    
for( i in 1:n){       
  for(j in 1:k){       
    z<-z+1        
    M[z,j]<-zt[z]    
  }    
  }  
M   } 
############################################  
M1<-MD(zt)  
MA<-matrix(0,(n*k-k*p),k*p)   
MAW<-matrix(0,(n*k-k*p),k*p)  
W1<-kronecker(diag(n), W)   
ztw<-W1%*%zt   
M2<-MD(ztw)  
zt<-as.matrix(zt)  
ZT<-zt[-(1:(k*p)),]   
for (i in 1:p){     MA[(1:(n*k-k*p)),(k*(i-1)+1):(k*((i-1)+1))]<-M1[(k*(p-i)+1):(n*k-(k*i)),]    
MAW[(1:(n*k-k*p)),(k*(i-1)+1):(k*((i-1)+1))]<-M2[(k*(p-i)+1):(n*k-(k*i)),]   }  
XT<-MA   
WXT<-MAW   
GSTAR<-data.frame(ZT,XT,WXT)   
GSTARfit<-lm(ZT~.-1,data=GSTAR)  
fit<-summary(GSTARfit)   
MSE<-(fit$sigma)^2   
MAE<-sum(abs(GSTARfit$residuals))/(n*k-k*p)  
MAPE<-sum(abs(GSTARfit$residuals)/ZT)/(n*k-k*p)   
MADP<-sum(abs(GSTARfit$residuals))/sum(ZT)  
AIC<-AIC(GSTARfit)   
R2<-fit$r.squared  
R2a<-fit$adj.r.squared   
Coef<-GSTARfit$coefficients   
Error<-data.frame(MSE=MSE, MAE=MAE, MAPE=MAPE, MADP=MADP, AIC=AIC, Rsquare=R2, AdjRSquare=R2a)   
Coefficient<-data.frame(Coef)   
Zt<-as.data.frame(matrix(ZT,n-p,k,byrow=T))  
Zhat1<-as.data.frame(matrix(GSTARfit$fitted.values,(n-p),k,byrow = T))   
Residual<-as.data.frame(matrix(GSTARfit$residuals,(n-p),k,byrow = T))  
Result<-data.frame(Zt,Zhat1)  
Result<-ts(Result)  


plot(Series,plot.type="single", lty=1:3, col = 6:2,xlab="Time",main="Data Series Plot")   
plot(Result,plot.type="multiple", lty=1:3, col = 6:2,main="Predictive vs Observed")  

plot(Result,plot.type="single", lty=1:3, col = 6:2,main="Predictive vs Observed")  
Residual<-ts(Residual)  
  
plot(Residual,plot.type="single", lty=1:3, col = 6:2,main="Residual")   
Summary<-list(GOF=Error,Fit=fit)   
return(GSTARfit) } 
#' Select the Best p #' @param p #' @return p #' @export 
Model<-function(p){   
  Error<-matrix(0,p,7)   
  for (i in 1:p){     Error[i,]<-as.matrix(GSTAR(Data,W,i)[[1]])   }   
  colnames(Error)<-c("MSE", "MAE", "MAPE", "MADP", "AIC", "Rsquare", "AdjRSquare") 
  Result<-list(Error=Error)  
  return(Result) }
